CALLING ALL FRIENDS, FAMILY, RACERS, FOLLOWERS, & LOCALS!!!! Please, we need your support this Thursday Dec 15th, 2022 at the Manatee County Administrative Center (starts at 9am, could go all day) to respectfully OPPOSE the application of a 2700 acre land use change. Taylor ranch is trying to convert 2700 acres from agricultural to allowing 3 homes per acre!!! If this goes through it will allow 4500 homes to be built right next door to Bradenton’s historic 50 years running racetracks! This is NOT a compatible use of the adjacent property. We need as many supporters as we can, doesn’t matter where you’re from, ANYONE can speak… Myself and a few other people are prepared to speak on the behalf of the tracks, but if you support our racetracks all you need to do is step before the commissioners and say “I OPPOSE”. Please come if you’re available and be as respectful as you can. DEFEND BRADENTON’S RACETRACKS!!!!
This is in regard to Application PA-21-09/Ordinance 23-11 PLN2111-0048

Breaking news!!!! Full story on Competition Plus! Link in bio!  NHRA Pro Modified Will Be Featured On The Primary “NHRA On FOX” Broadcasts
For the first time in the history of Pro Modified Drag Racing, fans of the action-packed and awe- inspiring FuelTech NHRA Pro Mod Drag Racing Series presented by Type A Motorsports will watch their favorite class of drag racing, during race day, on television. The ultra-competitive category will be featured during the primary Sunday broadcast of NHRA drag racing on FS1 and FOX for all ten Pro Mod races.
Two-time NHRA Pro Mod world champion and category advocate Stevie “Fast” Jackson is part of the wider team responsible for securing guaranteed air time on each broadcast for the 10 Pro Mod events featured on this year’s NHRA Camping World Drag Racing Series schedule.
“I’ve been to hundreds of racing events and the number one question I get asked is, when will fans get to see Pro Mods on the main TV broadcast,” said Jackson. “We have listened to you (the fans) because we love you, and here it comes. We are excited to deliver Pro Mod on the big show!” Jackson went on to say “I am just a small part of a rock star group of folks who are as passionate and in love with Pro Modified as I am. There are a bunch of people that have sacrificed a lot to bring NHRA Pro Mod to the level it’s at now, and I am proud to work with some of the best in the business.”

Holy Smokes! Hot Hot Hot off the presses!

NHRA Pro Mod To Feature New Playoff-Style Points Competition 

NHRA Pro Mod announces $425,000 plus purse for 2023 making it The Richest Sanctioned Door Car Series in History

Finish Line Consultants and NHRA officials announced today a new points system will be introduced for the FuelTech NHRA Pro Mod Drag Racing Series presented by Type A Motorsports during the 2023 season.
 
The Road to the Championship will incorporate a playoff-style competition similar to the NHRA Camping World Drag Racing Series Countdown to the Championship. This modification is part of a larger initiative to showcase the fan-favorite category more prominently in the NHRA.
 
The first of 10 overall events in the FuelTech NHRA Pro Mod Drag Racing Series presented by Type A Motorsports begins with the 54th annual Amalie Motor Oil NHRA Gatornationals on March 9-12. The regular season will conclude at the sixth event of the Pro Mod year, the Summit Racing Equipment NHRA Nationals in Norwalk on June 22-25. The event in Norwalk will also feature a points-and-a-half format for the standout competitors in the Pro Mod ranks, meaning the winner of the race will earn 150 points.
 
Following the race in Norwalk, the top 10 drivers in the points standings – along with those who meet the minimum qualifying requirements at all six regular-season races – will compete in the Road to the Championship over the final four NHRA Pro Mod events of the year in Brainerd, Indy, St. Louis and the finale at the NHRA Nevada Nationals at The Strip at Las Vegas Motor Speedway on Oct. 26-29. Those final four races will determine the 2023 world champion in the FuelTech NHRA Pro Mod Drag Racing Series presented by Type A Motorsports, with a points-and-a-half format also in place in Las Vegas.  Full story at https://www.nhra.com/news/2023/nhra-pro-mod-feature-new-playoff-style-points-competition-2023.  Link in bio

Don Schumacher was not only a passionate drag racer and competitor, but he was an innovator, a pioneer, and a Legend. 
Don fundamentally changed how the game was played. 
He went toe to toe with other racers, team owners, and stood his ground with NHRA. 
I first met Don in 2008 when I was trying to put a Nitro deal together and he gave me some advice I have followed my entire career. 
“Being good on the racetrack isn’t good enough, what you do off the track is far more important. Find what makes you different than everyone else and be great at it” he said. Drag Racing lost an Icon today. You will be missed.
